Package: MemTrajR
Title: Quantify Micron-Scale Rigid Domain Dynamics and Interactions
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Anthony", "Prempeh",
    role = c("aut", "cre"),
    email = "anthonynaprempeh@gmail.com",
    comment = c(ORCID = ""))
Description: Provides tools for analysing 2D and 3D membrane domain
    trajectories from single-particle tracking data. Functions cover
    mean squared displacement (MSD) computation in both Euclidean (2D)
    and geodesic (3D) geometries, early-time linear and power-law
    fitting, diffusion coefficient estimation, frame-by-frame geodesic
    separation analysis, interaction potential estimation via Boltzmann
    analysis, and mean square separation increment (MSSep) calculation.
    Designed for micron-scale rigid domain dynamics on spherical vesicles.
